article.description: — Nelly Cummings had a career-high 25 points as Colgate topped Northeastern 65-58 on Tuesday night in the season opener for both teams.
article.headline: Cummings scores 25 to lift Colgate over Northeastern 65-58
article.linkText: Cummings scores 25 to lift Colgate over Northeastern 65-58
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. -- — Nelly Cummings had a career-high 25 points as Colgate topped Northeastern 65-58 on Tuesday night in the season opener for both teams. Cummings hit 5 of 6 3-pointers. Tucker Richardson had 12 points and seven rebounds for Colgate. Ryan Moffatt added seven rebounds. Jeff Woodward had four assists. Jahmyl Telfort had 17 points for the Huskies (0-1). Chris Doherty added 14 points and eight rebounds. Shaquille Walters had 10 points and seven rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
